00:02:33.650 --> 00:02:38.020

        AND PSYCHIATRISTS AND FRIENDS
        THAT WE FEEL EMPTY INSIDE.
      

00:02:38.020 --> 00:02:44.100

        NEVER BEFORE, IT SEEMS, HAS SO
        MUCH MEANT SO LITTLE TO SO MANY.
      

00:02:44.100 --> 00:02:47.000

        Man:
        THERE'S A UNIVERSAL FEELING
	IN THIS NATION
      

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:49.800

        THAT WE'VE BECOME
        TOO MATERIALISTIC, TOO GREEDY
      

00:02:49.800 --> 00:02:51.800

        TOO SELFISH, TOO SELF-ABSORBED


00:02:51.800 --> 00:02:54.670

        AND THAT WE NEED TO BRING
        BACK INTO BALANCE
      

00:02:54.670 --> 00:02:55.970

        THE ENDURING VALUES


00:02:55.970 --> 00:03:00.510

        THAT HAVE GUIDED
        THIS COUNTRY OVER GENERATIONS.
      

00:03:00.510 --> 00:03:03.150

        Simon:
        SOME CALL THE AFFLICTION
	"AFFLUENZA"
      

00:03:03.150 --> 00:03:08.350

        UNTREATED, IT CAN CAUSE
        PERMANENT DISCONTENT.
      

00:03:08.350 --> 00:03:11.290

        AFFLUENZA'S COSTS
        AND CONSEQUENCES FOR US
      

00:03:11.290 --> 00:03:13.630

        FOR OUR FAMILIES AND COMMUNITIES


00:03:13.630 --> 00:03:16.860

        FOR FUTURE GENERATIONS
        AND THE EARTH ITSELF--
      

00:03:16.860 --> 00:03:19.870

        ARE IMMENSE,
        THOUGH OFTEN CONCEALED.
      

00:03:19.870 --> 00:03:21.830

        WE HUMAN BEINGS,
        ESPECIALLY IN THIS CENTURY
      

00:03:21.830 --> 00:03:23.670

        HAVE BEEN PRODUCING
        AND CONSUMING
      

00:03:23.670 --> 00:03:26.610

        AT A RATE THAT FAR EXCEEDS
        THE ABILITY OF THE PLANET
      

00:03:26.610 --> 00:03:29.940

        TO EITHER ABSORB OUR POLLUTION
        OR REPLENISH THE STOCK.
      

00:03:29.940 --> 00:03:31.210

        IT'S GOING
        TO HURT A BIT.
      

00:03:31.210 --> 00:03:33.510

        Simon:
        AFFLUENZA CAN BE CURED
      

00:03:33.510 --> 00:03:37.150

        BUT THE VIRUS
        IS VERY CONTAGIOUS.
      

00:03:37.150 --> 00:03:39.790

        ( growling ):
        BUY NOW, PAY LATER.
      

00:03:39.790 --> 00:03:45.460

        Simon:
        AND IT'S BEEN SPREADING
	FOR QUITE A WHILE.
      

00:03:45.460 --> 00:03:49.260

        Woman:
         I WANT A CORVETTE
      

00:03:49.260 --> 00:03:52.500

         I WANT A PONTIAC, TOO.


00:03:52.500 --> 00:03:55.600

        Man:
         LET'S GO ALL OUT
	AND BUY A CADILLAC, TOO.
      

00:03:55.600 --> 00:04:00.410

        Woman:
         I CAN HARDLY WAIT
	FOR THIS DREAM TO COME TRUE.
      

00:04:00.410 --> 00:04:03.180

        Simon:
        ARE YOU OLD ENOUGH
	TO REMEMBER THE '50S
      

00:04:03.180 --> 00:04:07.410

        THAT GOLDEN AGE OF PROSPERITY
        FOLLOWING THE SECOND WORLD WAR?
      

00:04:07.410 --> 00:04:10.380

        Announcer:
        IT'S A GREAT LIFE, EH, BOB?
      

00:04:10.380 --> 00:04:12.990

        AND TOMORROW
        WILL BE EVEN BETTER
      

00:04:12.990 --> 00:04:23.360

        FOR YOU AND FOR ALL THE PEOPLE.


00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:26.870

        Simon:
        WE FELT RICHER THEN
	THAN WE DO NOW.
      

00:04:26.870 --> 00:04:32.670

        A FAMOUS BOOK OF THE TIME CALLED
        AMERICA "THE AFFLUENT SOCIETY."
      

00:04:32.670 --> 00:04:35.670

        A BOOK WHOSE TITLE
        WOULD BE LAUGHABLE TODAY.
      

00:04:35.670 --> 00:04:38.910

        PEOPLE WOULD REJECT IT,
        EVEN THOUGH WE HAVE
      

00:04:38.910 --> 00:04:42.950

        ACTUALLY, IN TERMS OF GROSS
        NATIONAL PRODUCT AND SO FORTH
      

00:04:42.950 --> 00:04:44.680

        MORE THAN TWICE AS MUCH.


00:04:44.680 --> 00:04:48.320

        EVERYBODY'S HOME HAS GOT
        TWICE AS MUCH STUFF IN IT.
      

00:04:48.320 --> 00:04:49.820

        Simon:
        BACK IN 1958
      

00:04:49.820 --> 00:04:54.360

        ONLY FOUR PERCENT OF
        AMERICAN HOMES HAD DISHWASHERS.
      

00:04:54.360 --> 00:04:56.130

        NOW MORE THAN HALF DO.


00:04:56.130 --> 00:04:58.230

        LESS THAN ONE PERCENT
        HAD COLOR TELEVISIONS.
      

00:04:58.230 --> 00:05:00.870

        NOW IT'S 97%.


00:05:00.870 --> 00:05:04.840

        AND THERE WERE NO MICROWAVES,
        V.C.R.s OR PERSONAL COMPUTERS.
      

00:05:04.840 --> 00:05:06.470

        Man:
        UH... FOUR-CAR GARAGE?
      

00:05:06.470 --> 00:05:08.840

        IT'S PROBABLY
        BECAUSE OF STORAGE.
      

00:05:08.840 --> 00:05:11.040

        YOU NEVER HAVE
        ENOUGH STORAGE
      

00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:13.950

        AND SO, YOU KNOW,
        YOU NEVER HAVE ENOUGH GARAGES.
      

00:05:13.950 --> 00:05:15.450

        Simon:
        NEVER ENOUGH.
      

00:05:15.450 --> 00:05:18.120

        SO MUCH STUFF, SO LITTLE SPACE


00:05:18.120 --> 00:05:20.150

        EVEN THOUGH
        THE AVERAGE NEW HOUSE
      

00:05:20.150 --> 00:05:22.150

        HAS GROWN LARGER EVERY DECADE.


00:05:22.150 --> 00:05:25.020

        NOW MANY NEW HOMES
        HAVE THREE-CAR GARAGES--
      

00:05:25.020 --> 00:05:28.430

        NEARLY 900 SQUARE FEET
        OF GARAGE SPACE ALONE
      

00:05:28.430 --> 00:05:31.660

        WHICH IS ALMOST THE SIZE OF
        AN ENTIRE HOME IN THE '50s.
      

00:05:31.660 --> 00:05:34.870

        OH, DARLING,
        IT'S GOING TO BE
	JUST PERFECT!
      

00:05:34.870 --> 00:05:36.700

        Announcer:
        YOU ARE ABOUT TO ENTER
      

00:05:36.700 --> 00:05:39.200

        A BEAUTIFUL, EXCITING,
        WONDERFUL NEW WORLD--
      

00:05:39.200 --> 00:05:41.340

        THE WORLD OF 1960...


00:05:41.340 --> 00:05:45.180

        A WONDERFUL NEW WORLD OF FORDS.


00:05:45.180 --> 00:05:46.480

        Simon:
        IN THAT GILDED NEW WORLD
      

00:05:46.480 --> 00:05:48.650

        HARDLY ANY NEW CARS
        HAD AIR CONDITIONING.
      

00:05:48.650 --> 00:05:50.580

        TODAY, MORE THAN 90% DO.


00:05:50.580 --> 00:05:53.420

        ECONOMY CARS NOW OFFER
        MORE FEATURES
      

00:05:53.420 --> 00:05:55.120

        THAN LUXURY CARS DID THEN.


00:05:55.120 --> 00:05:56.890

        Woman:
        COLOR IS IMPORTANT.
      

00:05:56.890 --> 00:05:59.960

        I DON'T WORRY TOO MUCH
        ABOUT GAS MILEAGE AT ALL.
      

00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:02.230

        IT'S NOT SOMETHING
        THAT I LOOK AT.
      

00:06:02.230 --> 00:06:03.300

        A LOT OF MONEY.


00:06:03.300 --> 00:06:04.860

        YES, IT IS.


00:06:04.860 --> 00:06:07.970

        Simon:
        TODAY'S HOTTEST-SELLING CARS
      

00:06:07.970 --> 00:06:10.240

        ARE EXPENSIVE, GAS-HUNGRY
        SPORT UTILITY VEHICLES.
      

00:06:10.240 --> 00:06:12.940

        FOR A LOT OF PEOPLE,
        IT'S A STATUS SYMBOL.
      

00:06:12.940 --> 00:06:16.510

        SO THEY'RE WILLING TO SPEND THE
        30 TO 40-ODD THOUSAND DOLLARS
      

00:06:16.510 --> 00:06:18.480

        TO DRIVE ONE OF THESE VEHICLES.


00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:20.650

        Announcer:
        YES, FUN TO SEE
      

00:06:20.650 --> 00:06:21.950

        FUN TO DRIVE


00:06:21.950 --> 00:06:24.480

        FUN TO BUY--


00:06:24.480 --> 00:06:27.220

        THE NEW CHEVROLET.


00:06:27.220 --> 00:06:29.790

        Simon:
        JUST AS THEY DID IN THE '50s
      

00:06:29.790 --> 00:06:32.790

        NEW CARS STILL HELP US
        KEEP UP WITH THE JONESES.
      

00:06:32.790 --> 00:06:35.890

        BUT THESE DAYS, WE FIND IT
        MORE APPEALING TO FLY.
      

00:06:35.890 --> 00:06:39.800

        WE FLY 25 TIMES
        AS MUCH AS WE DID THEN.
      

00:06:39.800 --> 00:06:43.000

        SOMETIMES WE FLY JUST TO SHOP.


00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:44.400

        Woman:
        DON'T JUST STAND THERE--
      

00:06:44.400 --> 00:06:46.310

        GIVE ME YOUR CREDIT CARD!


00:06:46.310 --> 00:06:49.880

         WELL, THOSE EAST COAST STORES
        REALLY KNOCK ME OUT 
      

00:06:49.880 --> 00:06:51.640

         THEY LEAVE
        THE WEST BEHIND... 
      

00:06:51.640 --> 00:06:54.180

        Simon:
        POTOMAC MILLS ATTRACTS
	MORE VISITORS
      

00:06:54.180 --> 00:06:56.220

        THAN ANY OTHER SITE IN VIRGINIA.


00:06:56.220 --> 00:07:00.190

        THIS SHOPPING MALL IS SUCH
        A POPULAR TOURIST DESTINATION
      

00:07:00.190 --> 00:07:03.390

        AIRLINES OFFER EXCURSION FLIGHTS
        HERE FROM DISTANT CITIES.
      

00:07:03.390 --> 00:07:04.520

        WHERE ARE
        YOU FROM?
      

00:07:04.520 --> 00:07:05.930

        DALLAS AREA.


00:07:05.930 --> 00:07:08.930

        Simon:
        POTOMAC MILLS IS
	A DISCOUNT SUPERMALL
      

00:07:08.930 --> 00:07:12.870

        DIVIDED INTO WHAT
        ARE EUPHEMISTICALLY
	CALLED "NEIGHBORHOODS."
      

00:07:12.870 --> 00:07:16.900

        SHOPPING MALLS HAVE BECOME
        THE CENTERS OF MANY COMMUNITIES.
      

00:07:16.900 --> 00:07:20.440

        CHILDREN, AS WELL AS ADULTS,
        SEE A SHOPPING CENTER
      

00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:24.410

        AS JUST THE NATURAL DESTINATION
        TO FILL A BORED LIFE.
      

00:07:24.410 --> 00:07:27.750

        Simon:
        70% OF US VISIT MALLS EACH WEEK
      

00:07:27.750 --> 00:07:29.820

        MORE THAN ATTEND
        CHURCHES OR SYNAGOGUES.
      

00:07:29.820 --> 00:07:32.850

        ON AVERAGE, WE SHOP
        SIX HOURS A WEEK
      

00:07:32.850 --> 00:07:36.760

        AND SPEND ONLY 40 MINUTES
        PLAYING WITH OUR CHILDREN.
      

00:07:36.760 --> 00:07:39.930

        YOU SHOP,
        YOU SPEND MONEY--
	WHAT ELSE MATTERS?
      

00:07:39.930 --> 00:07:42.530

        Announcer:
        IT'S A HAPPY-GO-SPENDING WORLD
      

00:07:42.530 --> 00:07:45.930

        REFLECTED IN THE WINDOWS OF
        THE SUBURBAN SHOPPING CENTERS
      

00:07:45.930 --> 00:07:47.400

        WHERE THEY GO TO BUY.


00:07:47.400 --> 00:07:49.170

        Simon:
        BY 1987
      

00:07:49.170 --> 00:07:54.070

        AMERICA HAD MORE SHOPPING MALLS
        THAN HIGH SCHOOLS.
      

00:07:54.070 --> 00:07:56.680

        FEW MALL SHOPPERS COME
        WITH ANY INTENTION
      

00:07:56.680 --> 00:07:58.910

        OF PURCHASING
        A PARTICULAR PRODUCT.
      

00:07:58.910 --> 00:08:00.480

        MOST BUY LARGELY ON IMPULSE.


00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:02.550

        Woman:
        OOH, PARTY SNACKS!
      

00:08:02.550 --> 00:08:06.420

        Simon:
        AS THIS OLD SALES TRAINING FILM
	SUGGESTS, THAT'S NO ACCIDENT
      

00:08:06.420 --> 00:08:10.490

        Man:
        AND HERE'S THAT MOST IMPORTANT
	STORE DECISION OF ALL:
      

00:08:10.490 --> 00:08:12.020

        THE IMPULSE PURCHASE.


00:08:12.020 --> 00:08:12.930

        TO MAKE
        PEOPLE
	HUNGRY
      

00:08:12.930 --> 00:08:14.230

        FOR AS MUCH
        AS POSSIBLE--
      

00:08:14.230 --> 00:08:15.930

        HUNGRY ENOUGH
        TO BUY A LOT MORE
      

00:08:15.930 --> 00:08:17.060

        THAN THEY
        PLANNED TO.
      

00:08:17.060 --> 00:08:18.900

        Woman:
        Buy the half-price dress.
      

00:08:18.900 --> 00:08:20.770

        The cocktail party will come.


00:08:20.770 --> 00:08:23.970

        Have you been
        to Potomac Mills this month?
      

00:08:23.970 --> 00:08:26.440

        Simon:
        IT WAS AN INGRATIATINGLY
	CLEVER AD CAMPAIGN
      

00:08:26.440 --> 00:08:30.240

        THAT FIRST LURED ME
        TO POTOMAC MILLS MALL.
      

00:08:30.240 --> 00:08:31.180

        Shopping is therapy.


00:08:31.180 --> 00:08:33.910

        Listen to that little voice
        in your head.
      

00:08:33.910 --> 00:08:35.950

        Shop... shop... shop... shop...


00:08:35.950 --> 00:08:37.780

        You can buy happiness--


00:08:37.780 --> 00:08:40.090

        just don't pay retail for it.


00:08:40.090 --> 00:08:41.420

        Simon:
        BUT EVEN WHOLESALE
      

00:08:41.420 --> 00:08:44.760

        THE PRICE IS HIGHER THAN MOST
        OF US SEEM ABLE TO AFFORD.
      

00:08:44.760 --> 00:08:46.290

        IN FACT


00:08:46.290 --> 00:08:49.930

        THE PERCENTAGE OF AMERICANS
        CALLING THEMSELVES "VERY HAPPY"
      

00:08:49.930 --> 00:08:52.330

        REACHED ITS HIGHEST POINT
        BACK IN 1957.
      

00:08:52.330 --> 00:08:55.330

        THE PSYCHOLOGICAL REALITY
        OF PEOPLE IS
      

00:08:55.330 --> 00:09:00.210

        THAT ALMOST THEIR ENTIRE
        ORIENTATION TO HOW WE ARE DOING
      

00:09:00.210 --> 00:09:01.910

        IS BASED ON COMPARISON.


00:09:01.910 --> 00:09:04.310

        THAT'S WHY
        AS AN ENTIRE SOCIETY GROWS
      

00:09:04.310 --> 00:09:06.180

        PEOPLE DON'T FEEL ANY BETTER


00:09:06.180 --> 00:09:09.910

        BECAUSE THEY'RE STILL
        IN THE SAME RELATIVE POSITION.
      

00:09:09.910 --> 00:09:13.750

        THERE'S THIS SENSE OF BEING
        ON AN ENDLESS TREADMILL
      

00:09:13.750 --> 00:09:15.390

        AND OF NEVER GETTING


00:09:15.390 --> 00:09:19.090

        TO WHERE YOU THOUGHT
        YOU WERE GOING TO GET.
      

00:09:19.090 --> 00:09:22.130

        Simon:
        STILL, WE KEEP ON INCREASING
	OUR CONSUMPTION
      

00:09:22.130 --> 00:09:27.970

        PARTLY BY SAVING LESS
        AND WORKING MORE.
      

00:09:27.970 --> 00:09:31.370

        IN OUR RESEARCH, WE HEAR
        THE SAME REFRAIN ALL THE TIME:
      

00:09:31.370 --> 00:09:32.470

        "I HAVE NO LIFE.


00:09:32.470 --> 00:09:33.800

        "I GET UP IN THE MORNING


00:09:33.800 --> 00:09:35.710

        "DAY CARE, ELDER CARE...


00:09:35.710 --> 00:09:38.710

        "A 20- TO 40- MINUTE
        COMMUTE TO WORK.
      

00:09:38.710 --> 00:09:40.180

        "I HAVE TO WORK LATE.


00:09:40.180 --> 00:09:41.210

        "I GET HOME AT NIGHT.


00:09:41.210 --> 00:09:43.280

        "THERE'S LAUNDRY, BILLS TO PAY


00:09:43.280 --> 00:09:46.150

        "JAM SOMETHING
        INTO THE MICROWAVE OVEN.
      

00:09:46.150 --> 00:09:48.450

        "I'M EXHAUSTED,
        GO TO SLEEP, WAKE UP
      

00:09:48.450 --> 00:09:51.090

        AND THE ROUTINE BEGINS
        THE NEXT DAY ALL OVER AGAIN."
      

00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:54.130

        THIS IS WHAT LIFE
        HAS BECOME IN AMERICA.
      

00:09:54.130 --> 00:09:55.830

        WOULD JESUS BE
        AGENDA-DRIVEN?
      

00:09:55.830 --> 00:09:57.560

        WOULD HE CARRY
        A BEEPER?
      

00:09:57.560 --> 00:09:58.500

        CAN YOU IMAGINE HIM


00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:00.760

        GETTING BEEPED OUT
        OF THE LAST SUPPER?
      

00:10:00.760 --> 00:10:02.530

        Simon:
        RICHARD SWENSON, M.D.
      

00:10:02.530 --> 00:10:05.800

        HE COULD BE CALLED
        AN "AFFLUENZA EPIDEMIOLOGIST."
      

00:10:05.800 --> 00:10:10.280

        Swenson:
        IF YOU LOOK AT THE COUNTRIES
	THAT HAVE THE MOST PROSPERITY
      

00:10:10.280 --> 00:10:12.710

        THEY ARE THE SAME COUNTRIES
        THAT HAVE THE MOST STRESS.
      

00:10:12.710 --> 00:10:14.480

