00:29:16.850 --> 00:29:19.260

        "AND THEN EVENTUALLY
        WE DIVORCED OUR SPOUSES
      

00:29:19.260 --> 00:29:20.860

        AND WE GOT TOGETHER."


00:29:20.860 --> 00:29:22.430

        ONCE THE
        WRAPPING WAS OFF
      

00:29:22.430 --> 00:29:25.130

        THEN IT WASN'T AS NEW
        AND DIFFERENT AND WONDERFUL
      

00:29:25.130 --> 00:29:27.000

        AS IT WAS IN THE VERY BEGINNING


00:29:27.000 --> 00:29:29.730

        WHEN EVERYONE WAS DRESSED UP
        AND POWDERED
      

00:29:29.730 --> 00:29:31.000

        AND LOOKED PERFECT.


00:29:31.000 --> 00:29:32.600

        SO THEY GO BACK TO THE COMPANY


00:29:32.600 --> 00:29:35.140

        AND FIND SOME OTHER TOY
        TO PLAY WITH.
      

00:29:35.140 --> 00:29:36.470

        ( people exchanging farewells )


00:29:36.470 --> 00:29:39.140

        Simon:
        OUR COMMUNITY BONDS ALSO SUFFER.
      

00:29:39.140 --> 00:29:40.980

        THE SALVATION ARMY REPORTS
        DIFFICULTY
      

00:29:40.980 --> 00:29:43.310

        FINDING VOLUNTEER BELL RINGERS.


00:29:43.310 --> 00:29:45.620

        PARTICIPATION IN CIVIC
        ORGANIZATIONS AND ACTIVITIES
      

00:29:45.620 --> 00:29:47.980

        HAS BEEN DECLINING
        OVER THE PAST 20 YEARS.
      

00:29:47.980 --> 00:29:51.660

        Stanton:
        ALL OUR ATTENTION IS BEING
	PULLED IN THE WRONG DIRECTION.
      

00:29:51.660 --> 00:29:54.990

        IN TRYING TO RUN THAT RAT RACE,
        WE DON'T HAVE TIME
      

00:29:54.990 --> 00:29:59.100

        TO VOLUNTEER DOWN AT THE SOUP
        KITCHEN, TO VOLUNTEER AT CHURCH
      

00:29:59.100 --> 00:30:01.300

        TO GO VISIT THE OLD FOLKS' HOME


00:30:01.300 --> 00:30:09.040

        TO PAY SOME TIME AND ATTENTION
        TO PEOPLE WHO NEED US.
      

00:30:09.040 --> 00:30:13.010

        Simon:
        AFFLUENZA AFFECTS PEOPLE
	ACROSS ALL INCOME BARRIERS:
      

00:30:13.010 --> 00:30:15.310

        PEOPLE WHO HAVE A LOT
        BUT WANT MORE
      

00:30:15.310 --> 00:30:19.280

        THEN FEEL THEMSELVES ALMOST
        EMPTY INSIDE ONCE THEY GET MORE
      

00:30:19.280 --> 00:30:21.180

        AND PEOPLE WHO WANT
        FOR LIFE'S BASICS
      

00:30:21.180 --> 00:30:23.390

        BUT STILL FEEL THEMSELVES
        ALMOST TAUNTED
      

00:30:23.390 --> 00:30:24.950

        BY GLITTERING EMBELLISHMENTS.


00:30:24.950 --> 00:30:26.360

        AND IN RECENT YEARS


00:30:26.360 --> 00:30:29.060

        THE GAP BETWEEN THE TWO GROUPS
        HAS BEEN GROWING.
      

00:30:29.060 --> 00:30:32.800

        IN FACT, THE GAP BETWEEN RICH
        AND POOR AMERICANS IS NOW
      

00:30:32.800 --> 00:30:35.400

        THE WIDEST IN ANY
        INDUSTRIAL NATION.
      

00:30:35.400 --> 00:30:38.430

        LOW-INCOME PEOPLE SEE IT
        AS AN ISSUE OF INEQUITY:
      

00:30:38.430 --> 00:30:41.440

        HOW IS IT THAT I SEE
        ALL THESE PEOPLE AROUND ME
      

00:30:41.440 --> 00:30:45.080

        GETTING WEALTHIER AND WEALTHIER,
        DOING BETTER AND BETTER
      

00:30:45.080 --> 00:30:47.210

        GAINING MORE AND MORE
        MATERIAL GOODS
      

00:30:47.210 --> 00:30:50.850

        AT A TIME WHEN I'M FALLING
        FARTHER AND FARTHER BEHIND?
      

00:30:50.850 --> 00:30:56.190

        IF YOU LOOK CAREFULLY AT THE BIG
        CONSUMER BOOM SINCE THE 1980s
      

00:30:56.190 --> 00:30:58.320

        I THINK ONE OF THE THINGS
        YOU'LL FIND
      

00:30:58.320 --> 00:31:00.660

        IS THAT IT'S FAIRLY
        HEAVILY CONCENTRATED
      

00:31:00.660 --> 00:31:04.960

        IN THE UPPER PART
        OF THE MIDDLE CLASS AND ABOVE.
      

00:31:04.960 --> 00:31:07.530

        Simon:
        FELICIA EDWARDS DIDN'T SHARE
	IN THE BOOM.
      

00:31:07.530 --> 00:31:09.970

        SHE AND HER TWO SONS LIVE
        IN A TINY APARTMENT
      

00:31:09.970 --> 00:31:11.370

        IN HARTFORD, CONNECTICUT.


00:31:11.370 --> 00:31:12.940

        ( sighing heavily )


00:31:12.940 --> 00:31:15.070

        Simon:
        LIKE MANY LOW-INCOME AMERICANS
      

00:31:15.070 --> 00:31:17.640

        FELICIA WORKS FULL TIME
        AND THEN SOME
      

00:31:17.640 --> 00:31:20.680

        BUT STILL STRUGGLES
        TO PROVIDE FOR HER CHILDREN.
      

00:31:20.680 --> 00:31:25.950

        Edwards:
        I TRY TO TEACH THEM, YOU KNOW,
	A DOLLAR IS HARD TO COME BY ...
      

00:31:25.950 --> 00:31:27.220

        WELL, TO ME IT IS.


00:31:27.220 --> 00:31:30.050

        CHRISTMAS ROLLS AROUND:
        "CAN YOU BUY ME THIS?"
      

00:31:30.050 --> 00:31:32.920

        BUT WHATEVER I GIVE THEM,
        THEY'RE FINE WITH IT.
      

00:31:32.920 --> 00:31:35.190

        THEY DON'T ASK ANOTHER QUESTION.


00:31:35.190 --> 00:31:37.260

        MONEY IS NOT ALL THAT IMPORTANT.


00:31:37.260 --> 00:31:42.530

        I MEAN, WE CAN'T BUY CERTAIN
        THINGS, BUT STILL, WE'RE HAPPY.
      

00:31:42.530 --> 00:31:44.200

        WE'RE OKAY WITH IT.


00:31:44.200 --> 00:31:46.570

        Announcer:
        It's "Rocko's
	MODERN LIFE..."
      

00:31:46.570 --> 00:31:50.210

        Simon:
        YET FELICIA KNOWS HER BOYS
	FREQUENTLY FEEL DEPRIVED.
      

00:31:50.210 --> 00:31:51.940

        NOT LONG AGO,
        ONE OF THEM BEGGED HER
      

00:31:51.940 --> 00:31:54.040

        FOR A PAIR
        OF EXPENSIVE SNEAKERS.
      

00:31:54.040 --> 00:31:55.910

        Edwards:
        THEY WERE $90.
      

00:31:55.910 --> 00:31:59.980

        I HAD TO EXPLAIN TO HIM FIRST
        THAT I COULDN'T AFFORD THEM
      

00:31:59.980 --> 00:32:02.180

        SO HE WASN'T GOING TO GET THEM.


00:32:02.180 --> 00:32:05.120

        BUT ME AND HIS AUNT
        CAME TO A DECISION
      

00:32:05.120 --> 00:32:10.260

        THAT WE WAS GOING TO GO HALF
        ON THEM AND HE GOT THE SNEAKERS.
      

00:32:10.260 --> 00:32:14.800

        Simon:
        IN OUR POOREST COMMUNITIES, THE
	SENSE OF DEPRIVATION IS INTENSE.
      

00:32:14.800 --> 00:32:17.030

        Celente:
        THERE WAS A FELLOW THAT I MET
      

00:32:17.030 --> 00:32:18.130

        AND HE WORKS WITH GANGS


00:32:18.130 --> 00:32:21.200

        AND I ASKED HIM, "WHAT'S
        THE ONE THING THAT YOU SEE
      

00:32:21.200 --> 00:32:23.710

        THAT'S CAUSING A LOT
        OF THESE PROBLEMS?"
      

00:32:23.710 --> 00:32:28.510

        WITHOUT SKIPPING A BEAT, HE
        SAID, "GREED AND MATERIALISM."
      

00:32:28.510 --> 00:32:29.780

        HE SAID


00:32:29.780 --> 00:32:32.580

        "THESE KIDS, THEY DON'T FEEL
        LIKE THEIR LIVES
      

00:32:32.580 --> 00:32:35.980

        "WOULD BE WORTH ANYTHING UNLESS
        THEY HAD THE HOTTEST PRODUCT
      

00:32:35.980 --> 00:32:38.660

        THAT'S BEING SOLD
        IN THE MARKETPLACE."
      

00:32:38.660 --> 00:32:42.490

        Simon:
        SOON, CHILDREN THROUGHOUT
	THE WORLD MAY FEEL THE SMAE WAY.
      

00:32:42.490 --> 00:32:46.260

        Man:
        THE WHOLE CORPORATE SYSTEM
	IN THE COURSE OF GLOBALIZATION
      

00:32:46.260 --> 00:32:49.970

        IS INCREASINGLY GEARED UP
        TO BRING EVERY COUNTRY
      

00:32:49.970 --> 00:32:52.040

        INTO THE CONSUMER SOCIETY.


00:32:52.040 --> 00:32:54.070

        AND THERE'S
        A VERY STRONG EMPHASIS
      

00:32:54.070 --> 00:32:55.910

        ON TRYING TO REACH CHILDREN


00:32:55.910 --> 00:32:59.240

        TO RESHAPE THEIR VALUES
        FROM THE VERY BEGINNING
      

00:32:59.240 --> 00:33:03.550

        TO CONVINCE THEM THAT PROGRESS
        IS DEFINED BY WHAT THEY CONSUME.
      

00:33:03.550 --> 00:33:06.880

        Simon:
        EACH DAY, TELEVISION
	EXPOSES MILLIONS OF PEOPLE
      

00:33:06.880 --> 00:33:10.150

        IN THE DEVELOPING WORLD
        TO THE CONSUMER DREAM
      

00:33:10.150 --> 00:33:12.460

        AND THEY ARE EAGER
        TO BE INCLUDED.
      

00:33:12.460 --> 00:33:14.720

        DAVID KORTEN ONCE BELIEVED
        THEY COULD, AND SHOULD.
      

00:33:14.720 --> 00:33:17.530

        HE'S WORKED IN AFRICA, ASIA
        AND CENTRAL AMERICA
      

00:33:17.530 --> 00:33:20.660

        FOR THE HARVARD BUSINESS SCHOOL,
        THE FORD FOUNDATION
      

00:33:20.660 --> 00:33:23.000

        AND THE AGENCY FOR
        INTERNATIONAL DEVELOPMENT.
      

00:33:23.000 --> 00:33:26.200

        Korten:
        MY CAREER WAS FOCUSED
	ON TRAINING BUSINESS EXECUTIVES
      

00:33:26.200 --> 00:33:31.580

        TO CREATE THE EQUIVALENT OF
        OUR HIGH-CONSUMPTION ECONOMIES
      

00:33:31.580 --> 00:33:34.210

        IN COUNTRIES
        THROUGHOUT THE WORLD.
      

00:33:34.210 --> 00:33:36.240

        GRADUALLY I REALIZED
        THAT THAT WASN'T WORKING
      

00:33:36.240 --> 00:33:37.810

        AND COULDN'T WORK.


00:33:37.810 --> 00:33:40.420

        MANY PEOPLE'S LIVES
        WERE ACTUALLY WORSE OFF
      

00:33:40.420 --> 00:33:43.050

        THAT WE WERE SEEING
        THE ENVIRONMENT TRASHED.
      

00:33:43.050 --> 00:33:49.220

        WE WERE SEEING THE BREAKDOWN OF
        CULTURES AND THE SOCIAL FABRIC.
      

00:33:49.220 --> 00:33:53.160

        Simon:
        ONE-FIFTH OF THE WORLD'S PEOPLE
	LIVE IN ABJECT POVERTY
      

00:33:53.160 --> 00:33:56.730

        DYING SLOWLY OF HUNGER
        AND DISEASE.
      

00:33:56.730 --> 00:33:59.070

        MILLIONS OF OTHERS
        ALSO DESPERATELY NEED
      

00:33:59.070 --> 00:34:00.570

        MORE MATERIAL GOODS.


00:34:00.570 --> 00:34:02.870

        YET WERE THEY TO CONSUME
        AS MUCH AS WE DO
      

00:34:02.870 --> 00:34:06.810

        THE RESULT COULD BE
        AN ENVIRONMENTAL CRISIS.
      

00:34:06.810 --> 00:34:10.510

        THERE IS ABSOLUTELY NO WAY
        THAT EVERYONE IN THE WORLD
      

00:34:10.510 --> 00:34:13.080

        CAN LIVE AT THAT STANDARD
        OF AFFLUENCE
      

00:34:13.080 --> 00:34:16.450

        BECAUSE THE EARTH'S ECOSYSTEM
        SIMPLY WILL NOT STAND IT.
      

00:34:16.450 --> 00:34:19.320

        IMAGINE IF EVERY CHINESE
        HOUSEHOLD HAD TWO CARS.
      

00:34:19.320 --> 00:34:21.530

        Simon:
        AS THIS CAR SHOW
	IN BEIJING REVEALS
      

00:34:21.530 --> 00:34:23.890

        THEY'RE ALREADY ON THAT ROAD.


00:34:23.890 --> 00:34:25.930

        WESTERN PRODUCTS AND ADVERTISING


00:34:25.930 --> 00:34:28.200

        ARE POURING INTO
        DEVELOPING COUNTRIES.
      

00:34:28.200 --> 00:34:31.330

        IT IS CREATING A GROUNDWORK
        FOR A GLOBAL DISASTER.
      

00:34:31.330 --> 00:34:33.800

        Simon:
        COMBINED WITH
	A POPULATION EXPLOSION
      

00:34:33.800 --> 00:34:35.770

        NOT EXPECTED TO PEAK
        FOR DECADES
      

00:34:35.770 --> 00:34:39.580

        THE CONSUMPTION BOOM THREATENS
        TO DEVOUR THE WORLD'S RESERVES
      

00:34:39.580 --> 00:34:41.210

        OF OIL AND OTHER RESOURCES


00:34:41.210 --> 00:34:44.150

        WITHIN THE LIFETIME
        OF OUR GRANDCHILDREN.
      

00:34:44.150 --> 00:34:45.550

        WE'VE SET THE EXAMPLE.


00:34:45.550 --> 00:34:47.220

        Film narrator:
        THE AMERICAN CONSUMER.
      

00:34:47.220 --> 00:34:51.220

        EACH YEAR YOU CONSUME FANTASTIC
        AMOUNTS OF FOOD, CLOTHING
      

00:34:51.220 --> 00:34:55.590

        HOUSING, AMUSEMENTS, APPLIANCES
        AND SERVICES OF ALL KINDS...
      

00:34:55.590 --> 00:34:59.490

        Simon:
        SINCE 1950, AMERICANS ALONE
	HAVE USED MORE RESOURCES
      

00:34:59.490 --> 00:35:18.310

        THAN EVERYONE WHO EVER LIVED
        BEFORE THEM.
      

00:35:18.310 --> 00:35:23.420

        EACH OF US USES UP TO 20 TONS
        OF BASIC RAW MATERIALS ANNUALLY.
      

00:35:23.420 --> 00:35:25.960

        ONLY A SMALL FRACTION
        GETS RECYCLED.
      

00:35:25.960 --> 00:35:29.030

        Korten:
        WE ARE RUTHLESSLY CUTTING DOWN
	THE WORLD'S FORESTS
      

00:35:29.030 --> 00:35:32.660

        DEGRADING OUR LANDS,
        DESTROYING THE CLIMATIC SYSTEMS
      

00:35:32.660 --> 00:35:34.600

        ALL IN THE QUEST FOR MONEY.


00:35:34.600 --> 00:35:38.100

        Simon:
        WE AMERICANS THROW AWAY
	SEVEN MILLION CARS A YEAR
      

00:35:38.100 --> 00:35:40.400

        TWO MILLION PLASTIC BOTTLES
        EVERY HOUR
      

00:35:40.400 --> 00:35:45.780

        ENOUGH ALUMINUM CANS ANNUALLY
        TO MAKE 6,000 DC-10 AIRLINERS.
      

00:35:45.780 --> 00:35:50.180

        THE TOTAL YEARLY WASTE WOULD
        FILL A CONVOY OF GARBAGE TRUCKS
      

00:35:50.180 --> 00:35:55.950

        LONG ENOUGH TO REACH
        HALFWAY TO THE MOON.
      

00:35:55.950 --> 00:35:59.760

        OUR RIVERS AND OCEANS ARE
        ALREADY CLOTTED WITH POLLUTION.
      

00:35:59.760 --> 00:36:02.760

        INCREASED EMISSIONS OF
        CARBON DIOXIDE AND OTHER GASES
      

00:36:02.760 --> 00:36:05.300

        ACCELERATE GLOBAL WARMING.


00:36:05.300 --> 00:36:08.260

        Woman:
        AFFLUENZA, THE DISEASE
	OF CONSUMERISM
      

00:36:08.260 --> 00:36:10.570

        IS SPREADING AROUND THE WORLD


00:36:10.570 --> 00:36:14.200

        SO IT'S REALLY CRITICAL THAT
        WE HERE IN NORTH AMERICA BEGIN
      

00:36:14.200 --> 00:36:16.440

        TO ALTER OUR PATTERNS
        OF CONSUMPTION
      

00:36:16.440 --> 00:36:19.110

        AND SET A BETTER EXAMPLE
        FOR THE REST OF THE WORLD
      

00:36:19.110 --> 00:36:20.840

        OF WHAT THE GOOD LIFE REALLY IS


00:36:20.840 --> 00:36:24.180

        OR NONE OF US ARE GOING TO HAVE
        A GOOD LIFE.
      

00:36:24.180 --> 00:36:26.450

        Simon:
        ACCORDING TO HISTORIAN
	DAVID SHI
      

00:36:26.450 --> 00:36:30.620

        THE IDEA THAT THE GOOD LIFE IS
        A SIMPLER, LESS ACQUISITIVE LIFE
      

00:36:30.620 --> 00:36:32.390

        RUNS DEEP IN OUR HERITAGE.


00:36:32.390 --> 00:36:36.260

        Shi:
        SIMPLICITY IS AN ANCIENT,
	EVEN A PRIMORDIAL IDEAL.
      

00:36:36.260 --> 00:36:38.760

        THE GREEKS REFERRED TO IT
        AS THE "MIDDLE WAY"--
      

00:36:38.760 --> 00:36:42.030

        THAT MIDPOINT BETWEEN
        LUXURY AND DEPRIVATION.
      

00:36:42.030 --> 00:36:44.630

        Simon:
        "GIVE ME NEITHER POVERTY
	NOR RICHES"
      

00:36:44.630 --> 00:36:46.300

        READS THE BOOK OF PROVERBS.


00:36:46.300 --> 00:36:48.570

        THE NEW TESTAMENT IS FILLED
        WITH WARNINGS
      

00:36:48.570 --> 00:36:50.170

        ABOUT THE DANGERS OF WEALTH.


00:36:50.170 --> 00:36:52.940

        Shi:
        SO WHEN THE PURITANS ARRIVED
	IN THE NEW WORLD
      

00:36:52.940 --> 00:36:55.910

        ONE OF THEIR MAJOR PREMISES
        WAS THEIR DESIRE
      

00:36:55.910 --> 00:36:58.680

        TO TRY TO CREATE
        A CHRISTIAN COMMONWEALTH
      

00:36:58.680 --> 00:37:00.920

        THAT PRACTICED SIMPLE LIVING.


00:37:00.920 --> 00:37:04.290

        Simon:
        "WASTE NOT, WANT NOT,"
	WROTE BENJAMIN FRANKLIN
      

00:37:04.290 --> 00:37:05.820

        IN COLONIAL AMERICA


00:37:05.820 --> 00:37:09.130

        HABITS OF THRIFT PERSISTED
        ALONGSIDE DESIRES FOR LUXURY.
      

00:37:09.130 --> 00:37:10.960

        EVEN 19th-CENTURY AMERICANS


00:37:10.960 --> 00:37:14.730

        STILL HAD MORE RESPECT FOR
        THRIFT THAN FOR SPENDTHRIFTS
      

00:37:14.730 --> 00:37:17.770

        AND THE WORD "CONSUMPTION"
        MEANT SOMETHING DIFFERENT THEN.
      

00:37:17.770 --> 00:37:20.500

        Rifkin:
        IF YOU GO BACK TO SAMUEL
	JOHNSON'S DICTIONARY
      

00:37:20.500 --> 00:37:23.240

        OF THE ENGLISH LANGUAGE,
        "TO CONSUME" MEANT "TO EXHAUST
      

00:37:23.240 --> 00:37:25.170

        TO PILLAGE, TO LAY RENT,
        TO DESTROY."
      

00:37:25.170 --> 00:37:27.640

        IN FACT, EVEN IN OUR
        GRANDPARENTS' GENERATION
      

00:37:27.640 --> 00:37:30.880

        WHEN SOMEBODY HAD TUBERCULOSIS,
        THEY CALLED IT "CONSUMPTION."
      

00:37:30.880 --> 00:37:32.520

        SO, UP UNTIL THIS CENTURY


00:37:32.520 --> 00:37:35.450

        TO BE A CONSUMER WAS
        NOT TO BE A GOOD THING.
      

00:37:35.450 --> 00:37:37.720

        IT WAS CONSIDERED A BAD THING.


00:37:37.720 --> 00:37:40.490

        Simon:
        ONE OF THE FIRST HARBINGERS
	OF A CHANGE OF HEART
      

00:37:40.490 --> 00:37:41.990

        WAS THE DEPARTMENT STORE.


00:37:41.990 --> 00:37:46.100

        Woman:
        URBAN DEPARTMENT STORES CAME IN
	DURING THE 1880'S
      

00:37:46.100 --> 00:37:49.360

        BASICALLY TO CREATE THE SORT
        OF PLACE WHERE PEOPLE WOULD GO
      

00:37:49.360 --> 00:37:52.530

        AND KIND OF LOSE THEMSELVES
        AND SPEND THEIR MONEY.
      

00:37:52.530 --> 00:37:55.840

        Simon:
        BY THE 1890s, WEALTHY AMERICANS
	PROUDLY DISPLAYED
      

00:37:55.840 --> 00:37:58.140

        THE MATERIAL SIGNS
        OF THEIR SUCCESS.
      

00:37:58.140 --> 00:38:00.540

        STILL, NOT EVERYONE
        WAS IMPRESSED.
      

00:38:00.540 --> 00:38:04.450

        Shi:
        IN THE LATE 19th CENTURY,
	THER WAS ANOTHER MAJOR REVIVAL
      

00:38:04.450 --> 00:38:06.920

        OF AMERICAN INTEREST
        IN SIMPLE LIVING.
      

00:38:06.920 --> 00:38:10.050

        THEODORE ROOSEVELT WAS ONE
        OF THE FOREMOST PROPONENTS
      

00:38:10.050 --> 00:38:13.220

        OF A SIMPLER LIFE FOR AMERICANS
        DURING THIS PERIOD.
      

00:38:13.220 --> 00:38:15.520

        ROOSEVELT WAS QUITE CANDID
        IN SAYING
      

00:38:15.520 --> 00:38:18.730

        THAT FOR ALL OF HIS SUPPORT
        FOR AMERICAN CAPITALISM
      

00:38:18.730 --> 00:38:22.400

        HE FEARED THAT IF IT WERE
        ALLOWED TO DEVELOP UNLEASHED
      

00:38:22.400 --> 00:38:26.140

        IT WOULD EVENTUALLY CREATE
        A CORRUPT CIVILIZATION.
      

00:38:26.140 --> 00:38:30.270

        Simon:
        AS CONSUMER GOODS BEGAN TO ROLL
	IN LARGE QUANTITIES
      

00:38:30.270 --> 00:38:32.810

        FROM AMERICAN ASSEMBLY LINES


00:38:32.810 --> 00:38:34.610

        LABOR AND RELIGIOUS
        LEADERS URGED
      

00:38:34.610 --> 00:38:37.280

        THAT PRODUCTIVE
        NEW TECHNOLOGIES BE USED
      

00:38:37.280 --> 00:38:41.220

        TO GIVE PEOPLE MORE FREE TIME
        INSTEAD OF MORE POSSESSIONS.
      

00:38:41.220 --> 00:38:44.690

        BUT BUSINESS EXECUTIVES FEARED
        A LAG IN CONSUMER DEMAND
      

00:38:44.690 --> 00:38:46.960

        MIGHT SEND THE WHOLE ECONOMY
        CRASHING DOWN.
      

00:38:46.960 --> 00:38:49.390

        THEY CLAIMED THAT HUMAN WANTS
        WERE INSATIABLE
      

00:38:49.390 --> 00:38:52.300

        AND LOOKED TO PSYCHOLOGY
        TO STIMULATE SPENDING.
      

00:38:52.300 --> 00:38:53.760

        Announcer:
        WHY FEEL LOW?
      

00:38:53.760 --> 00:38:55.260

        WHY BE A LITTLE GUY?


00:38:55.260 --> 00:38:58.300

        NOW YOU CAN BE JUST AS TALL
        AS YOUR BEST GIRL.
      

00:38:58.300 --> 00:39:01.370

        SLIP INTO A PAIR
        OF UPSY-DAISY SHOES.
      

00:39:01.370 --> 00:39:03.440

        THEY GIVE YOU A LIFT.


00:39:03.440 --> 00:39:06.140

        Simon:
        AFTER THE GREAT DEPRESSION
	AND WORLD WAR II
      

00:39:06.140 --> 00:39:09.410

        A LIFT WAS JUST WHAT
        AMERICANS WANTED
      

00:39:09.410 --> 00:39:12.250

        AND BUSINESS WAS EAGER
        TO PROVIDE IT--
      

00:39:12.250 --> 00:39:14.220

        WITH SOME HELP
